  "prompt": "Can educational testing services (ETS) sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visa?",
  "response": "Educational Testing Service (ETS), like many other organizations, can potentially sponsor an H-1B visa. Whether they can sponsor a \"cap-exempt\" H-1B visa depends on specific circumstances related to the job and the organization's status. Generally, an employer is considered cap-exempt if it is:\n\n1. An institution of higher education.\n2. A nonprofit organization related to or affiliated with an institution of higher education.\n3. A nonprofit research organization.\n4. A governmental research organization.\n\nIf ETS fits one of these criteria or the job role aligns with such criteria, they might be able to sponsor a cap-exempt H-1B visa. However, it's essential for the organization and potential employee to consult with an immigration attorney to assess specific eligibility based on the latest immigration laws and individual circumstances.",
